# Eddie Vibe Marketer — Cursor Rules

## Architecture
- Node.js orchestrator in scripts/, Python publisher in publisher/
- All phase scripts are standalone: each reads from data/ and writes to data/
- No direct agent-to-agent communication — data passes through JSON files on disk
- Titan agents are prompt enhancers, not standalone processes

## Code Style
- Node scripts use require() (CommonJS), not ES modules
- dotenv loaded at top of each script with path to ../.env
- All file paths use path.resolve(__dirname, '..')
- Console output uses emoji prefixes for phase identification

## Content Rules
- Never post duplicate content
- No "test post" language on public platforms
- Short-form writing: no "Wh-" starters, no dramatic fragments
- Quality gate must pass before production

## Security
- API keys in .env only, never in code
- .env is gitignored
- Browser Use uses persistent Chrome profile — never store credentials in code
- --dry-run before live publishing

## Testing
- Run `npm run setup` to validate environment
- Use `--dry-run` flag on publisher before live runs
- Every pipeline change needs a full-cycle test with sample data
